### 7.5 Interpretation

The agent operates at the "Recursive Will" level, where R\_{\\text{int}}
\> 0. Empirical validation of non-zero R\_{\\text{int}} in RL agents can
be observed in the entropy evolution during training: a purely
deterministic agent exhibits monotonic entropy decay, while an agent
with active recursive feedback shows **entropy fluctuations correlated
with TD-error magnitude** \|\\delta\|, exactly as predicted by
R\_{\\text{int}} = \\eta \|\\delta\| C.

## 8. The Formalization of Self-Referential Will

### 8.1 The Meta-Recursive Leap

A system models its own recursive contradiction resolution.

